import sys

n = int(sys.stdin.readline().strip())
k1 = int(sys.stdin.readline().strip())
cards1 = list(map(int, sys.stdin.readline().strip().split(' ')))
k2 = int(sys.stdin.readline().strip())
cards2 = list(map(int, sys.stdin.readline().strip().split(' ')))

cards1 = cards1[0:k1]
cards2 = cards2[0:k2]

while len(cards1) > 0 and len(cards2) > 0:
    if cards1[0] > cards2[0]:
        cards1.append(cards1[0])
        cards1.append(cards2[0])
        cards1.pop(0)
        cards2.pop(0)
    elif cards1[0] < cards2[0]:
        cards2.append(cards2[0])
        cards2.append(cards1[0])
        cards2.pop(0)
        cards1.pop(0)
    else:
        cards1.append(cards1[0])
        cards1.append(cards2[0])
        cards1.pop(0)
        cards2.pop(0)

if len(cards1) > 0:
    print(len(cards1) + len(cards2), 1)
elif len(cards2) > 0:
    print(len(cards1) + len(cards2), 2)
else:
    print(-1)

def main():
    n = int(input())
    a = list(map(int, input().split()))
    b = list(map(int, input().split()))
    a.sort(reverse=True)
    b.sort(reverse=True)
    while a and b:
        if a[-1] > b[-1]:
            a.pop()
            b.pop()
            a.append(b[-1])
            b.pop()
            a.append(b[-1])
            b.pop()
        elif a[-1] < b[-1]:
            a.pop()
            b.pop()
            b.append(a[-1])
            a.pop()
            b.append(a[-1])
            a.pop()
        else:
            a.pop()
            b.pop()
            a.append(b[-1])
            b.pop()
            a.append(b[-1])
            b.pop()
    if a:
        print(len(a), 1)
    else:
        print(len(b), 2)


if __name__ == '__main__':
    main()
